 The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has appointed former Senate President Bukola Saraki as the Chairman of the National Reconciliation Committee. He is to head a six-member committee comprised of other eminent members of the party. The PDP disclosed this in his official Twitter handle @officialPDPNigeria Monday night. The members are a former Senate President, Pius Anyim; former Governors of Gombe State, Ibrahim Dankwambo; Liyel Imoke (Cross Rivers) and Ibrahim Shema (Katsina), as well as a former member of the House of Representatives, Mulikat Adeola.